escribed by a short burst of star formation occurring within a quiescent\ngalaxy, rather than by continuous star formation. A detailed discussion on the\ninferred parameters, such as the age, burst strength, metallicity, star\nformation rate, extinction and total stellar mass for individual objects, is\npresented in paper II of this series.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Sep 2002 10:31:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 20 Dec 2002 11:07:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
